content: It is so nice to see you here
Today it is our last lesson of tactics department.
maybe someday, it will be reopened
but now it goes to sleep
those who are worried about the future of the class,
please dont fear, I will not leave you.
I will try my best, to make you all happy.
if possible, the next department will have the life soon.
it will be the analytical department.
and someday after that, I will open the history department, for those who love to know about famous renju people and historical events and all.
meanwhile, the analytical class may go on,
under the guidance of new headmaster
so we might have 3 departments same time

slamduk, Chancewu, fallnavy, bomb, luwenzhe, leto, Ikon, Alan, cisco, moocheng, yyfcsd, eastmen, smiling, weigui, dadisheng, Southerner, Volodymyr, alcore, Intotherenju, amber, concord2497, nhaanx, whte.
today's topic is related to the special kind of tactics.
its not only related to the board and variants,
the emotions, the fear, the excitement, the nervousness, the courage, the bluff, and so on - all have very very important role.
If you want to be successful,
you have to learn more than just renju.
if you just learn renju, you will be at most a master
the psychological factor is very important in big games.
How many of you are read to win me?
actually, it may sound silly question,
but it makes all the difference.
if you are not ready to win, you will not win.
last world championship, I won 11 games.
nobody ready to beat you there
I was ready to win, wating to win.
and, I worked for win only.
the obstacles of the win are:
the opponent's strength and fame, and his knowledge.
many people have better knowledge than me sometimes,
but they cannot beat the fame
and they will make a mistake
in the situation where they maybe more expert than me
Most of you could win me, I believe.
but if you learn only renju, you cannot win so easily.
you have to learn about your opponent.
to see what he sees, to think what he thinks, to know what he knows.
dont learn only renju, but learn about people.
even renlib includes a free db
better one is the one the sinyov is distributing
you can email him and buy one
in last WC, I used the notebook
I spent hours to analyse his games,
not as much about his theory,
but to learn about his style, his tactics,
if he is a "safe" style player,
knowing that he will not dare to go for vctr
then I will give him attack opportunity instead
if he likes straight style, then give him the traps
where he will go and attack
I am sure he would go here
you can predict lots of things
and make a decision before the game
this is just a silly example on the board
but you know what I mean
try to find your opponents success.
and then find the weakness in it.
you are most likely to have guaranteed win.
I knew he had a successful variant,
he had 100% win rate there so far.
he will come with this variant against you,
his strong side became his weakness
and he doesnt even know it
you dont need to study all
but I trusted psychology more than theory
seldom a player changes his successful path for no reason
this 16-h11 is maybe 5% of all variants here.
do you think I studied the rest of the 95% here?
I didnt even look a second
I could have been in big trouble,
if he didnt go as I planned,
but I didnt worry so much,
psychology is more important factor in top games than theory
if you know what he will do,
then you dont need to study so much
Now, I will tell you a few words about the fame.
We all fear the strong and famous players in real tournaments.
maybe you can do well online,

slamduk, luwenzhe, Chancewu, leto, Ikon, bomb, nhaanx, whte, weigui, fallnavy, yyfcsd, shuwang, cisco, Southerner, eastmen, dadisheng, alcore, Intotherenju, concord2497, Volodymyr, smiling, moocheng, Alan.
but if you sit face to face,
I dont know how many of you have the chance to visit WC,
you will see lots of sweatting and hand shaking there
you will forget everything you had learned,
when the guy across the table is Nakamura.
the psychological tactics is to beat the fame.
can you sit there and think Nakamura isnt so strong after all?
can you think and not to "see" your opponent at all?
when I played with Nakamura, I could not stop thinking the whole first game "he is Nakamura, he is Nakamura, I am in trouble"
and I could not play a good game
you have all seen my ugly game
will have nakamura stories in history dpt?
I lost the game so fast,
because I was influenced by his fame
and could not stay focused and calm.
I had to get myself together,
in the second game, the only way I could break this psychological condition was to attack back
and put him into the deep thinking
when you put him into thinking,
and when he declined my bluff
and I felt I was mentally much better in this game already
actually, they are not important games int he aspect of theory
but the winner and loser is mostly decided by psychology
if you want to not to lose to the "fame", make your opponent "smaller"
think anything you can to help it
think he is old, think he has not prepared well, think he didnt have recent game experience,
think he maybe lost his job
and you will no longer feel bothered by his "fame".
when Nakamura went to smoking during game,
I calmed myself by thinking that its not doing good to him, and it forces him to leave table, break the focus
so, you have prepared against your opponent well,
dont just want to show a good game, or get draw,
or have the longest fight or something
if you are ready, and you want win,
I was not well prepared for last WC,
because I had evertyhing I needed to win the games.
but I made the right choice and preparation.
how many of you will join the WC in sweden this year?
either QT, or B tournament, or AT
i need to prepare for WC...
with your knowledge, you could be the stars there
B tournament is open for any level
you dont need to prepare much for B tournament
you need psychology if you have big ambitions
but you dont know how to succeed
How many of you have played in real renju tournament, with clocks and all?
many strong players dont get along with the clock
when the time is running out,
its recommended to play lots of short time games before big tournament
to get the sense of fast thinking
now, I want to talk about the ethics and behaviour in the tournament.
there is an article by Ando
you do the procedure of thinking
and later compare with real outcome
some people cannot visualize all the cuts
when you practics, and compare later with putting the stones on the board,
then you will see what you missed.
then next time you will try to pay more attention on the weakness.
after long time, you will notice that so many renju patterns are same
you will almost "know" if there is win or not
to do the same job as talented people
I think, Sushkov is maybe more talented than me, Nakamura too
but you did better than them
but like in every sport, you can always learn good techique
sometimes the variant is too long,
maybe my opponent is having same problem
like with my game with Nikonov in last wc
he had a  moment where he could win
it was so hard for me to see its end
now, about the behaviour of the players
you know, there is a big difference between online and real games
in real tournaments, players do not cheat.
thats why I like the real games.
renju family in the world is very kind and respectful,
but sometimes, when newcomer enters the tournament,
he may not know about good traditions and manners,
and he will do something that makes everybody upset.
so, it is very good if you prepare yourself before the tournament
in fact, most trouble situations happened in China.
because at that time, China was quite new for world's renju.
and the players didnt know what is good and bad.
and now they are doing well.
do not leave the tournament room while the game is not over.
if you have to leave the room for some reason, please be accompanied by a referee
a player who got very high place in BT,
he was naive, thought that it will not be noticed.
do not talk if you are playing,
and do not bother the playing person
if you have to talk to someone, especially to your countrymate,
one country's coach was telling hints to his student in their language
and the opponent could not do anything
the complaint was made to the referee,
but referee was too kind and forgiving
such things will take down the reputation as a player
and its almost impossible to earn back
so, if you want to become a respected player,
many people forget to shake hands before game,
and even worse - they will not shake hand after game when they lose
if you can show your respect by congratulating your opponent after your loss,
then you have shown you are a great man
in reality, not always like this though
but there is a relation between skill and mannetr
for example, AT players tend to be very polite
they will often even bow to opponent when shake hands
the most confusing thing is the language
when you are a chinese man
and you talk to your countrymate
i think it's a part of renju
you will feel so big temptation to speak chinese
dont think that because you are a honest man,
so its allright to speak your language
please remember, others dont know that!
when I talk to Ants during wc game
and usually we walk near the referee
so that referee can hear our talk
when games are over, we speak Estonian language again
did anyone of you have such experience of international tournament?
maybe the Asian Cup will be held in autumn,
then all this becomes very important
you will know what makes you a true and respected player.
there are no clear RIF rules for placing the stones
do not adjust the ugly stone while its not your turn
many people start the beauty adjustment, while opponent is thinking
same hand that plays the move, hits the clock
each player must keep the record of the game on paper
you should write down every move, before making next move,
some people violate this rule often
some people make series of moves
but this is wrong and unpolite
because, you are "stealing" your opponents time
even if the oppnent plays a four
many players just block it immediately
and then write down both moves
actually, take your time, be calm and polite
take a breath, and then block the four
for all these small things, people will admire and respect you.
this first time to join the big tournament is the toughest
if you dont know these rules of manners,
and you can do well, and act well.
then I must thank you all for your great patience you showed today,
and if there are no questions,
then I will announce the tactics department to be closed.
Thank you all dearest friends, I was glad to be here.
Alan, alcore, bomb, Chancewu, cisco, concord2497, dadisheng, eastmen, Ikon, Intotherenju, leto, luwenzhe, nhaanx, slamduk, smiling, Southerner, Volodymyr, weigui, whte, yyfcsd.
